# Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** March 1, 2026

Thank you for choosing to play **Kid Smart** ("we", "us", or "our"). This Privacy Policy describes how your information is handled in our application, Kid Smart (the "App"). We are committed to protecting the privacy of our users, especially children. 

## 1. Information Collection and Use

**We do not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal information from our users.** 

The App is designed to provide a safe and self-contained experience. Any data generated during gameplay (such as scores or game progress) is stored entirely locally on your device. We do not transmit this data to our servers, nor do we share it with any third parties.

## 2. Children's Privacy (COPPA & Google Play Families Policy Compliance)

We take children's privacy very seriously. Our App is designed specifically for children aged 5 years and under. We comply with the strict requirements of the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) in the US, as well as Google Play's Families Policy and User Data policy for apps whose primary target audience is children. 

- We do not knowingly collect, request, or maintain any personal information from anyone, including our target audience of children aged 5 years and under. 
- We do not use personalized or targeted advertising.
- We do not track users across other apps or websites.

If a parent or guardian believes that we have unintentionally collected personal information from a child, please contact us immediately so we can take steps to remove such information.

## 3. Third-Party Services and Advertising

The App **does not** integrate with third-party analytics platforms, tracking mechanisms, or data-collection SDKs. We do not display third-party advertisements.

## 4. Device Permissions

The App only requests permissions that are strictly necessary for its core functionality (e.g., access to speakers for game audio). We do not use device permissions to access or extract personal data, contacts, location, or files.

## 5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

